<subSubSection id="C353654BFFCDFFDE59B1C075D908FAE3" pageId="2" pageNumber="392" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BF636C0FFCDFFDE59B1C075DEDAFB06" blockId="2.[151,1436,748,1500]" pageId="2" pageNumber="392">
<emphasis id="B93DEAD2FFCDFFDE59B1C075DA46FCC8" bold="true" box="[151,269,784,807]" pageId="2" pageNumber="392">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Head longer than wide (
<figureCitation id="13722A45FFCDFFDE5B32C075D91FFCC8" box="[532,596,784,807]" captionStart="FIGURES5–11" captionStartId="3.[151,258,1819,1841]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,191,1754]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,191,1797]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES5–11. Bangithrips mei. (5)head &amp;pronotum;(6)antenna; (7) pro-&amp; mesosterna;(8) meso-&amp; metanota,pelta &amp;tergite II; (9)sternites VIII–X; (10) tergites VIII–X; (11)fore leg." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1208868/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="392">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
), not prolonged in front of eyes; posterior ocelli close to large compound eyes; vertex very weakly sculptured except near ocelli and along posterior margin; postocular setae long and finely pointed, placed laterally and well behind eyes; maxillary stylets probably deeply retracted and close together (dissociated in available two specimens), mandible small. Antennae 8-segmented (
<figureCitation id="13722A45FFCDFFDE5A50C01DD8F2FC60" box="[886,953,888,911]" captionStart="FIGURES5–11" captionStartId="3.[151,258,1819,1841]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,191,1754]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,191,1797]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES5–11. Bangithrips mei. (5)head &amp;pronotum;(6)antenna; (7) pro-&amp; mesosterna;(8) meso-&amp; metanota,pelta &amp;tergite II; (9)sternites VIII–X; (10) tergites VIII–X; (11)fore leg." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1208868/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="392">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
); segment II sharply angled with distinctive hump on inner margin, campaniform sensillum in basal half; III–VIII with faint closely spaced transverse sculpture lines; III–V each with 2 short, fat sense cones, VI–VII each with one sense cone; VIII elongate and slender. Pronotal shield with no long setae (
<figureCitation id="13722A45FFCDFFDE5849C085DAFAFC18" box="[367,433,992,1015]" captionStart="FIGURES5–11" captionStartId="3.[151,258,1819,1841]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,191,1754]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,191,1797]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES5–11. Bangithrips mei. (5)head &amp;pronotum;(6)antenna; (7) pro-&amp; mesosterna;(8) meso-&amp; metanota,pelta &amp;tergite II; (9)sternites VIII–X; (10) tergites VIII–X; (11)fore leg." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1208868/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="392">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
), epimeral setae long, notopleural sutures incomplete; basantra absent (
<figureCitation id="13722A45FFCDFFDE5D9CC085DFB6FC18" box="[1210,1277,992,1015]" captionStart="FIGURES5–11" captionStartId="3.[151,258,1819,1841]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,191,1754]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,191,1797]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES5–11. Bangithrips mei. (5)head &amp;pronotum;(6)antenna; (7) pro-&amp; mesosterna;(8) meso-&amp; metanota,pelta &amp;tergite II; (9)sternites VIII–X; (10) tergites VIII–X; (11)fore leg." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1208868/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="392">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
); ferna widely separated; mesopraesternum reduced to two small sclerites, mesoeusternal margin entire. Mesonotum weakly reticulate, lateral setae long (
<figureCitation id="13722A45FFCDFFDE5845C740DAEDFBD3" box="[355,422,1061,1084]" captionStart="FIGURES5–11" captionStartId="3.[151,258,1819,1841]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,191,1754]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,191,1797]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES5–11. Bangithrips mei. (5)head &amp;pronotum;(6)antenna; (7) pro-&amp; mesosterna;(8) meso-&amp; metanota,pelta &amp;tergite II; (9)sternites VIII–X; (10) tergites VIII–X; (11)fore leg." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1208868/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="392">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
); metanotum longitudinally reticulate, median setal pair long and acute. Fore wing parallelsided, with about 14 duplicated cilia, with two relatively short sub-basal setae. Fore femur robust with long setae on inner margin ventrally, tarsal tooth large and robust (
<figureCitation id="13722A45FFCDFFDE5BADC70FD993FB6E" box="[651,728,1130,1153]" captionStart="FIGURES5–11" captionStartId="3.[151,258,1819,1841]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,191,1754]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,191,1797]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES5–11. Bangithrips mei. (5)head &amp;pronotum;(6)antenna; (7) pro-&amp; mesosterna;(8) meso-&amp; metanota,pelta &amp;tergite II; (9)sternites VIII–X; (10) tergites VIII–X; (11)fore leg." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1208868/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="392">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
); fore coxae large, each with a long seta. Mid and hind tibiae each with two very stout setae. Pelta broadly triangular (
<figureCitation id="13722A45FFCDFFDE5BF1C7E8D857FB4B" box="[727,796,1165,1188]" captionStart="FIGURES5–11" captionStartId="3.[151,258,1819,1841]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,191,1754]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,191,1797]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES5–11. Bangithrips mei. (5)head &amp;pronotum;(6)antenna; (7) pro-&amp; mesosterna;(8) meso-&amp; metanota,pelta &amp;tergite II; (9)sternites VIII–X; (10) tergites VIII–X; (11)fore leg." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1208868/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="392">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
); tergite II lateral margins eroded; III–VII with no wingretaining setae; tergite IX setae shorter than tube (
<figureCitation id="13722A45FFCDFFDE5B9DC7D5D840FB28" box="[699,779,1200,1223]" captionStart="FIGURES5–11" captionStartId="3.[151,258,1819,1841]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,191,1754]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,191,1797]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES5–11. Bangithrips mei. (5)head &amp;pronotum;(6)antenna; (7) pro-&amp; mesosterna;(8) meso-&amp; metanota,pelta &amp;tergite II; (9)sternites VIII–X; (10) tergites VIII–X; (11)fore leg." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1208868/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="392">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
); tube little longer than wide (
<figureCitation id="13722A45FFCDFFDE5D7CC7D5DFD6FB28" box="[1114,1181,1200,1223]" captionStart="FIGURES5–11" captionStartId="3.[151,258,1819,1841]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,191,1754]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,191,1797]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES5–11. Bangithrips mei. (5)head &amp;pronotum;(6)antenna; (7) pro-&amp; mesosterna;(8) meso-&amp; metanota,pelta &amp;tergite II; (9)sternites VIII–X; (10) tergites VIII–X; (11)fore leg." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1208868/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="392">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
), margins convex; anal setae shorter than tube. Sternites without reticulate areas, with transverse row of 6–8 setae; median marginal setae long.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF636C0FFCDFFDE59E1C790D908FAE3" blockId="2.[151,1436,748,1500]" box="[199,579,1268,1292]" pageId="2" pageNumber="392">
Type species 
<emphasis id="B93DEAD2FFCDFFDE5870C791D908FAE3" bold="true" box="[342,579,1268,1292]" pageId="2" pageNumber="392">
